     1	# ADR-004: Use Auth.js v5 for Authentication
     2	
     3	## Status
     4	Accepted
     5	
     6	## Context
     7	The application needs secure authentication (Email/Password), session management (30-day rolling), and role-based access control (Power User vs Managed User).
     8	
     9	## Decision
    10	We will use Auth.js v5 (NextAuth) with the Credentials provider and Prisma adapter.
    11	
    12	## Alternatives Considered
    13	- **Better Auth**: Newer and well-designed, but less AI training data available than Auth.js.
    14	- **Lucia Auth**: Deprecated by author in 2024.
    15	- **Custom JWT session**: More work to implement secure rolling refresh, CSRF protection, and edge middleware integration.
    16	
    17	## Consequences
    18	- **Benefits**: Native integration with Next.js App Router; large ecosystem; easy database persistence via Prisma adapter; handles complex auth flows out-of-the-box.
    19	- **Costs**: Learning curve for v5 beta patterns; some friction with custom "password reset" flows which must be implemented manually.
